AI MODEL LICENSES

The following AI models are NOT included in this repository and are subject
to their own licenses. Users must download and comply with individual model
licenses:

1. RealESRGAN
   License: BSD 3-Clause
   Authors: Xintao Wang et al., Tencent ARC Lab
   Commercial use: Allowed

2. GFPGAN
   License: Non-commercial research use only
   Authors: Xintao Wang et al., Tencent ARC Lab
   Commercial use: NOT ALLOWED without permission

3. BasicVSR++
   License: Apache 2.0
   Authors: Kelvin C.K. Chan et al., CUHK & SenseTime
   Commercial use: Allowed

4. SwinIR
   License: Apache 2.0
   Authors: Jingyun Liang et al., ETH Zurich
   Commercial use: Allowed

5. RIFE (Real-Time Intermediate Flow Estimation)
   License: MIT License
   Authors: Zhewei Huang et al., MEGVII Technology
   Commercial use: Allowed

6. DeOldify
   License: MIT License
   Author: Jason Antic
   Commercial use: Allowed

7. ProPainter
   License: Research/academic use (check original repository)
   Authors: Shangchen Zhou et al., S-Lab
   Commercial use: May be restricted - verify license

IMPORTANT NOTICE:
Users are responsible for ensuring compliance with all applicable AI model
licenses. Some models (notably GFPGAN and ProPainter) may restrict commercial
use. Check the ai_models/models/registry.yaml file for current license
information and source URLs.

================================================================================

COMMERCIAL USE DISCLAIMER

While this software (Advanced Tape Restorer) is MIT licensed and permits
commercial use, some bundled AI models may have restrictions. Users engaging
in commercial video restoration must:

1. Review individual AI model licenses in ai_models/models/registry.yaml
2. Obtain necessary permissions for restricted models
3. Consider using only commercially-licensed models (RealESRGAN, BasicVSR++,
   SwinIR, RIFE, DeOldify)
4. Disable or avoid models with non-commercial restrictions (GFPGAN, ProPainter)

For commercial licensing inquiries regarding future Pro version features
(network rendering, priority support), contact: [To be added]

